commit.message: Add GitHub CI for Ubuntu and macOS
Use gnulib base_name(), not basename() (thanks, @cho-m)

Don’t use libgc, just leak memory

mmv is a one-shot tool, so it’s unlikely that libgc would be collecting much
garbage for us anyway, and its use is a bit fragile: if malloc-related
symbols are not perfectly overridden (especially in gnulib), then crashes
can occur.
Remove calls to free(): rely on libgc
Use top_srcdir for path to opts.ggo
Compare only basename of program when deciding which mode to run in
configure.ac: bump version to 2.6

Reintroduce mad (append), requested by a user

This essentially reverts commits 8901464, e57a2ca and 38ab87c.

As well, remove the ZAPPEND flag, which only applied to MS/DOS, and add
.gitignore patterns for executables ending in .exe.
Bump version to 2.5.1

Revert gnulib update

This seems to cause a problem with the redefinition of malloc-related
functions and hence a crash in realloc (which should not be called).

Since we didn’t specifically need a newer gnulib, revert the update.

This reverts commit 2fdbd7e3eae920f838232560bbd5730f6fd1a5aa.
configure.ac: bump version to 2.5
README.md: clarify the name of the tarball, and that it must be unpacked
Do not try to move a folder into itself (fix #13)
mmv.c: fix one line that ended up mis-indented after previous deletions
README.md: add missing dependency pkg-config to list.
Remove special treatment of ‘!’, no longer a special character
Simplify breakout() function
Update gnulib
Use _GL_UNUSED instead of obsolete _GL_UNUSED_PARAMETER

Fix -D flag

mmv needs to be able to distinguish non-existent directories, so add a path
member to the DIRINFO struct.
Remove a redundant “return” statement at the end of a function
Reorder code to eliminate forward declarations of static functions
Replace fprintf to stdout with printf
Bump version to 2.4
Use make_path function (from bash) instead of mkdir(1)
Add the ability to create non-existent directories (-D flag)
Remove some excessive spacing
Use S_IRUSR and S_IWUSR instead of obsolete S_IREAD and S_IWRITE
Add some _GL_ATTRIBUTE_PURE annotations
Call _exit in signal handler, not (unsafe) exit
